{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Class","externalID":"s:3Gym7SwimmerC","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Swimmer","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Swimmer","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Swimmer","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"Gym"}]},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Swimmer"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Env","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/MuJoCoEnv"],"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gym\/swimmer"]}],"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Swimmer\/init(forwardRewardWeight:ctrlCostWeight:resetNoiseScale:)"],"title":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Swimmer\/data","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Swimmer\/model"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Swimmer\/Env-Implementations"],"generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["Linux"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Swimmer"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Description","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Description"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This environment corresponds to the Swimmer environment described in Rémi Coulom’s PhD thesis","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/tel.archives-ouvertes.fr\/tel-00003985\/document","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The environment aims to increase the number of independent state and control","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"variables as compared to the classic control environments. The swimmers","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"consist of three or more segments (’","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"links","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"text":"’) and one less articulation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"joints (’","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"rotors","type":"text"}]}]},{"text":"’) - one rotor joint connecting exactly two links to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"form a linear chain. The swimmer is suspended in a two dimensional pool and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"always starts in the same position (subject to some deviation drawn from an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"uniform distribution), and the goal is to move as fast as possible towards","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the right by applying torque on the rotors and using the fluids friction.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Notes","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Notes"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem parameters are:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Problem parameters:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":": number of body parts"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"m"},{"type":"text","text":"i"}]},{"type":"text","text":": mass of part "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"i","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"i","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" ∈ {1…n})"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"l"},{"type":"text","text":"i"}]},{"type":"text","text":": length of part "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"i","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"i"}]},{"type":"text","text":" ∈ {1…n})"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"k","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":": viscous-friction coefficient"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"While the default environment has "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" = 3, "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"l"},{"type":"text","text":"i"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" = 0.1,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"k"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" = 0.1. It is possible to pass a custom MuJoCo XML file during construction to increase the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"number of links, or to tweak any of the parameters."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Action Space","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Action-Space"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The action space is a ","type":"text"},{"code":"Box(-1, 1, (2,), float32)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". An action represents the torques applied between ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"links","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Num"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Action"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Control Min"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Control Max"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Joint","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Unit","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Torque applied on the first rotor"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"-1","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"1","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"motor1_rot","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"hinge","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"torque (N m)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Torque applied on the second rotor","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-1"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"motor2_rot","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"torque (N m)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"header":"row"},{"text":"Observation Space","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Observation-Space"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, observations consists of:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"θ"},{"type":"text","text":"i"},{"type":"text","text":": angle of part "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"i"}]},{"type":"text","text":" with respect to the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}]},{"type":"text","text":" axis"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"θ","type":"text"},{"text":"i","type":"text"},{"text":"’: its derivative with respect to time (angular velocity)","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In the default case, observations do not include the x- and y-coordinates of the front tip. These may","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be included by passing ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exclude_current_positions_from_observation=False"},{"text":" during construction.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Then, the observation space will have 10 dimensions where the first two dimensions","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"represent the x- and y-coordinates of the front tip.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Regardless of whether ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exclude_current_positions_from_observation"},{"text":" was set to true or false, the x- and y-coordinates","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will be returned in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"info"},{"text":" with keys ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"x_position\""},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"y_position\""},{"text":", respectively.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"By default, the observation is a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ndarray"},{"text":" with shape ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(8,)"},{"text":" where the elements correspond to the following:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"| Num | Observation                          | Min  | Max | Name (in corresponding XML file) | Joint | Unit                     |","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"| — | ———————————— | –– | — | –––––––––––––––– | —– | ———————— |","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"| 0   | angle of the front tip               | -Inf | Inf | free_body_rot                    | hinge | angle (rad)              |","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"| 1   | angle of the first rotor             | -Inf | Inf | motor1_rot                       | hinge | angle (rad)              |","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"| 2   | angle of the second rotor            | -Inf | Inf | motor2_rot                       | hinge | angle (rad)              |","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"| 3   | velocity of the tip along the x-axis | -Inf | Inf | slider1                          | slide | velocity (m\/s)           |","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"| 4   | velocity of the tip along the y-axis | -Inf | Inf | slider2                          | slide | velocity (m\/s)           |","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"| 5   | angular velocity of front tip        | -Inf | Inf | free_body_rot                    | hinge | angular velocity (rad\/s) |","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"| 6   | angular velocity of first rotor      | -Inf | Inf | motor1_rot                       | hinge | angular velocity (rad\/s) |","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"| 7   | angular velocity of second rotor     | -Inf | Inf | motor2_rot                             | hinge | angular velocity (rad\/s) |","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Rewards","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Rewards"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The reward consists of two parts:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"forward_reward","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A reward of moving forward which is measured"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"forward_reward_weight"},{"text":" * (x-coordinate before action - x-coordinate after action)\/dt","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":". "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"dt","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the time between actions and is dependent on the frame_skip parameter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(default is 4), where the frametime is 0.01 - making the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"default "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"dt = 4 * 0.01 = 0.04"}]},{"type":"text","text":". This reward would be positive if the swimmer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"swims right as desired."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"ctrl_cost","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":": A cost for penalising the swimmer if it takes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"actions that are too large. It is measured as "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ctrl_cost_weight"},{"type":"text","text":" *"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sum(action"},{"type":"text","text":"2"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" where "},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"ctrl_cost_weight","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" is a parameter set for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"control and has a default value of 1e-4"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The total reward returned is "},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"reward"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"="}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"forward_reward - ctrl_cost"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"info"},{"type":"text","text":" will also contain the individual reward terms"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Starting State","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Starting-State"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All observations start in state (0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0) with a Uniform noise in the range of [-","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reset_noise_scale"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reset_noise_scale"},{"text":"] is added to the initial state for stochasticity.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Episode End","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Episode-End"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The episode truncates when the episode length is greater than 1000."}]},{"text":"Arguments","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Arguments"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"No additional arguments are currently supported in v2 and lower.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["gym.make('Swimmer-v4')"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"v3 and v4 take gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["env = gym.make('Swimmer-v4', ctrl_cost_weight=0.1, ....)"]},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Parameter"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Type","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Default"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Description","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"xml_file"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"str"}],"type":"strong"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"swimmer.xml\""}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Path to a MuJoCo model","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"forward_reward_weight"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"float","type":"text"}]}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Weight for ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"forward_reward","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" term (see section on reward)","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"ctrl_cost_weight","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"float"}],"type":"strong"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"1e-4","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Weight for "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"ctrl_cost","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" term (see section on reward)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"reset_noise_scale","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"float"}]}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0.1"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scale of random perturbations of initial position and velocity (see section on Starting State)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"exclude_current_positions_from_observation","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"bool","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"True","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Whether or not to omit the x- and y-coordinates from observations. Excluding the position can serve as an inductive bias to induce position-agnostic behavior in policies"}]}]]],"header":"row"},{"text":"Version History","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Version-History"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"v4: all mujoco environments now use the mujoco bindings in mujoco>=2.1.3","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"v3: support for gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc. rgb rendering comes from tracking camera (so agent does not run away from screen)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"v2: All continuous control environments now use mujoco_py >= 1.50","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"v1: max_time_steps raised to 1000 for robot based tasks. Added reward_threshold to environments.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v0: Initial versions release (1.0.0)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]}],"references":{"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/Gym/Swimmer":{"title":"Swimmer","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Swimmer","abstract":[],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Swimmer","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gym\/swimmer","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Swimmer","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/Gym":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym","url":"\/documentation\/gym","title":"Gym","abstract":[],"role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"https://tel.archives-ouvertes.fr/tel-00003985/document":{"url":"https:\/\/tel.archives-ouvertes.fr\/tel-00003985\/document","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/tel.archives-ouvertes.fr\/tel-00003985\/document","title":"“Reinforcement Learning Using Neural Networks, with Applications to Motor Control”","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Reinforcement Learning Using Neural Networks, with Applications to Motor Control”"}]},"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/Gym/Swimmer/model":{"title":"model","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gym\/swimmer\/model","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentati